title: Secret Service agent who saved Reagan after shooting dies
text:
> Top News Secret Service agent who saved Reagan after shooting dies FILE - In this Feb. 27, 1985 file photo, President Ronald Reagan bids farewell to Jerry Parr, the Secret Service agent that he credited with saving his life during an assassination attempt on March 30, 1981. Parr retired after 22 years with the elite unit of bodyguards. Parr of Washington, D.C., died Friday at the age of 85. (AP Photo/Barry Thumma) iWitness7 is your chance to join the News Center 7 team!
